    </dt>

            title="">

        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>The provider-assigned unique ID for this managed resource.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-"
            title="">
        <span id="jobtype_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#jobtype_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Job<wbr>Type</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>

<strong>DATA_MIGRATION</strong>, <strong>UPDATE</strong>, <strong>DELETE</strong>, <strong>RESTART_QUEUE</strong> and <strong>SCALE_QUEUE</strong>.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-"
            title="">
        <span id="owner_csharp">

## Supporting Types



<h4 id="sqljobconf">Sql<wbr>Job<wbr>Conf</h4>

<div>
<pulumi-choosable type="language" values="csharp">
<dl class="resources-properties"><dt class="property-optional property-replacement"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="dlisqljobtimeout_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#dlisqljobtimeout_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Dli<wbr>Sql<wbr>Job<wbr>Timeout</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">int</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Sets the job running timeout interval. If the timeout interval
expires, the job is canceled. Unit: <code>ms</code>. Changing this parameter will create a new resource.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional property-replacement"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="dlisqlsqlasyncenabled_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#dlisqlsqlasyncenabled_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Dli<wbr>Sql<wbr>Sqlasync<wbr>Enabled</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">bool</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies whether DDL and DCL statements are executed
asynchronously. The value true indicates that asynchronous execution is enabled. Default value is <code>false</code>.
Changing this parameter will create a new resource.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional property-replacement"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="sparksqlautobroadcastjointhreshold_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#sparksqlautobroadcastjointhreshold_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Spark<wbr>Sql<wbr>Auto<wbr>Broadcast<wbr>Join<wbr>Threshold</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">int</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Maximum size of the table that
displays all working nodes when a connection is executed. You can set this parameter to -1 to disable the display.
Default value is <code>209715200</code>. Changing this parameter will create a new resource.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional property-replacement"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="sparksqlbadrecordspath_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#sparksqlbadrecordspath_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Spark<wbr>Sql<wbr>Bad<wbr>Records<wbr>Path</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Path of bad records. Changing this parameter will create
a new resource.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional property-replacement"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="sparksqldynamicpartitionoverwriteenabled_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#sparksqldynamicpartitionoverwriteenabled_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Spark<wbr>Sql<wbr>Dynamic<wbr>Partition<wbr>Overwrite<wbr>Enabled</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">bool</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>In dynamic mode, Spark does not delete
the previous partitions and only overwrites the partitions without data during execution. Default value is <code>false</code>.
Changing this parameter will create a new resource.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional property-replacement"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="sparksqlfilesmaxpartitionbytes_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#sparksqlfilesmaxpartitionbytes_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Spark<wbr>Sql<wbr>Files<wbr>Max<wbr>Partition<wbr>Bytes</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">int</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Maximum number of bytes to be packed into a
single partition when a file is read. Default value is <code>134217728</code>. Changing this parameter will create a new
resource.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional property-replacement"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="sparksqlmaxrecordsperfile_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#sparksqlmaxrecordsperfile_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Spark<wbr>Sql<wbr>Max<wbr>Records<wbr>Per<wbr>File</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">int</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Maximum number of records to be written
into a single file. If the value is zero or negative, there is no limit. Default value is <code>0</code>.
Changing this parameter will create a new resource.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional property-replacement"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="sparksqlshufflepartitions_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#sparksqlshufflepartitions_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Spark<wbr>Sql<wbr>Shuffle<wbr>Partitions</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">int</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Default number of partitions used to filter
data for join or aggregation. Default value is <code>4096</code>. Changing this parameter will create a new resource.</p>
</dd></dl>
</pulumi-choosable>

## Import



DLI SQL job can be imported by `id`. For example,

```sh
 $ pulumi import huaweicloud:Dli/sqlJob:SqlJob example 7f803d70-c533-469f-8431-e378f3e97123
```

 Note that the imported state may not be identical to your resource definition, due to some attributes missing from the API response, security or some other reason. The missing attributes include`conf`, `rows` and `schema`. It is generally recommended running `terraform plan` after importing a resource. You can then decide if changes should be applied to the resource, or the resource definition should be updated to align with the resource. Also you can ignore changes as below. resource "huaweicloud_dli_sql_job" "test" {

 ...

 lifecycle {

 ignore_changes = [

 conf, rows, schema

 ]

 } }
